# Progress logging rule

This project maintains a progress log at `docs/PROGRESS.md`.

## When making changes

- After completing any meaningful task/feature/bugfix, **append** a new entry under **Progress entries** in `docs/PROGRESS.md`.
- Each entry must include:
  - What was done (1–3 bullets)
  - Which roadmap part/task it maps to (from `docs/implementation_plan.md`)
  - Key files touched
  - Commit hash if a commit was created

## Format

- Use a dated heading like: `### YYYY-MM-DD — Part X: <name>`
- Keep entries concise; do not rewrite past entries.

